calculatePrice(uint8,bool).details: Calculates the price of minting a specified amount of tokens

params._amount: The amount of tokens to mint
params._isDiscounted: Whether the user is on the discount allowlist

returns._0: The price of minting the specified amount of tokens

checkDiscountMerkleProof(bytes32[],addre.details: Checks the validity of a discount Merkle proof for a given address.

params._address: The address for which the Merkle proof is being checked.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the Merkle proof is valid or not.

checkFreeClaimAllowlist(bytes32[],addres.details: Checks if a merkle proof is valid.

params._merkleProof: The merkle proof to be checked.

claim(address,uint8,bytes32[]).details: Allows to claim tokens for free using a merkle proof

params._amount: The amount of tokens to mint
params._recipient: The address to receive the minted tokens
params.proof: The merkle proof to be checked

params._baseUri: The base URI of the contract
params._initialOwner: The initial owner of the contract

getConfig().details: Returns the current configuration of the auction.

mint(address,uint8,bytes32[]).details: Mints a new token and assigns it to the specified recipient

params._amount: The amount of tokens to mint
params._recipient: The address to receive the minted token

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

ownerMint(address,uint16).details: Owner mints for free a new token and assigns it to the specified recipient

params._amount: The amount of tokens to mint
params._recipient: The address to receive the minted token

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setBaseURI(string).details: Sets the base URI for token URIsOnly the owner can call this function

setConfig(uint256,uint256).details: This function can only be called by an admin. It can be used to set the start time, end time,  minimum bid increment in WEI, and starting bid amount.

setDiscountAllowlistRoot(bytes32).details: Allows the owner to set the root of the discount allowlist merkle tree

params._allowlistRoot: The new root of the discount allowlist merkle tree

setFreeClaimAllowlistRoot(bytes32).details: Allows the owner to set the root of the free claim allowlist merkle tree

params._allowlistRoot: The new root of the free claim allowlist merkle tree

setFundsReceiverAddress(address).details: Sets the address of the funds receiverOnly the owner can call this function

params.newFundsReceiverAddress: The address of the funds receiver

setTokenPrice(uint256).details: Allows the owner to set the price of a token

params._tokenPrice: The new price of a token

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Checks if a specific interface is supported by the contract

returns._0: True if the interface is supported, false otherwise

tokenURI(uint256).details: Returns the URI of a specific token

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw().details: Withdraws the contract balance to the funds receiver addressOnly the owner can call this function

DISCOUNT_PERCENTAGE().notice: The amount of tokens that can be claimed for free.

FREE_CLAIM_AMOUNT().notice: The maximum number of tokens that can be minted at once.

regularMinted().notice: The number of tokens claimed for free.

setConfig(uint256,uint256).notice: Sets the configuration parameters for the auction.
